<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-625-191  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 625 191.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 13 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft ships MS-Word v5.5 in UK. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Ltd. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Microsoft Word 5.5 for Windows (Word processing software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionWord processing software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MICROSOFT SHIPS MS-WORD V5.5 IN UK  11/13/90 LONDON, ENGLAND, 1990 NOV 13(NB) -- Microsoft UK has announced the availability of MS-Word 5.5 forWindows.andP;  The new version features a visual user interface that provideseasier access to all features and and greater interfaceconsistency/compatibility with other members of the Microsoft Word family.andM;&quot;The number one request from our users was to make Word for DOS even easierto use,&quot; said Alan Dowzall, Word product manager with MIcrosoft UK.andM;&quot;We responded by dramatically improving the user interface, making Word mucheasier to use and providing better access to its leading feature set.andP;  Weremain committed to our character-based product, which is a worldwidebest-seller, and plan to continue to provide improvements beyond version5.5,&quot; he added.andM;In a brief hands-on with a beta-test version of the package - which ships inthe UK in late November - Newsbytes can report that the new interface isbased on a character-based graphical user interface.andP;  Commands are presentedvisually with pull-down menus and pop-up dialogue boxes.andM;Common commands are now presented visually along the top of the screen usinga ribbon and ruler system.andP;  The ribbon is one of concepts that Microsoft ispursuing with its GUI packages - this is the first time the ribbon has beenseen on a text-based package.andM;MS-Word version 5.5 for DOS will retail for UKP 395 for the single userversion.andP;  A five user networked package will sell for UKP 1,185.andP;  Systemrequirements have been pared to 384K of RAM (512K is recommended) plus twinfloppy drives.andM;(Steve Gold/19901109/Press andamp; Public Contact: Microsoft UK - Tel: 0734-391123)</TEXT></DOC>